tatus/1237126151753138184|title=Governor Steve Bullock embodies Montana's proud tradition of supporting good government and clean elections. He has successfully fought against corruption and worked to overturn Citizens United. We're proud to endorse @stevebullockmt for #MTSEN.|work=Twitter|date=March 9, 2020|accessdate=March 9, 2020}}</ref>\n}}\n\n===Results===\n{{Election box begin no change\n| title = Democratic primary results\n}}\n{{Election box  candidate with party link no change\n| candidate = [[Steve Bullock (American politician)|Steve Bullock]]\n| party = Democratic Party (United States)\n| votes = \n| percentage = \n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link no change\n| candidate = John Mues\n| party = Democratic Party (United States)\n| votes =\n| percentage = \n}}\n{{Election box total no change\n| votes = \n| percentage = 100.0%\n}}\n{{Election box end}}\n\n==Other Candidates==\n===Libertarian Party===\n'''Nominee'''\n*Susan Geise, [[Lewis and Clark County]] commissioner and former chair of the [[Montana Republican Party]]<ref>{{cite web |title=Geise enters 2020 run for U.S. Senate as Libertarian |url=https://www.greatfallstribune.com/story/news/2020/03/19/geise-enters-2020-run-u-s-senate-montana-libertarian/2878351001/ |website=Great Falls Tribune |date=March 20, 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Green Party===\n'''Declared'''\n*Dennis Daneke, retired college professor<ref>{{cite web |last1=Dennison |first1=Mike |title=MT Green Party candidates: One says, `don\u2019t vote for me\u2019 |url=https://www.ktvh.com/news/montana-news/mt-green-party-candidates-one-says-dont-vote-for-me |website=KTVH |date=March 26, 2020}}</ref>\n*Wendie Fredrickson, former audit reviewer for Montana State Department of Public Health and Human Services<ref name=\"MTsenc\"/>\n\n'''Results'''\n{{Election box begin no change\n| title = Green primary results\n}}\n{{Election box  candidate with party link no change\n| candidate = Dennis Daneke\n| party = Green Party (United States)\n| votes = 